Ask HN: I just saw ChatGPT working in parallel on a bulleted list?
text:
I ask it if there's easy way to represent a graph as in easy to understand text and it said a bulleted list. Which I'm not sure if that's the best answer.

But what was interesting was each of the bullets had cursors blinking like it was working on each of them in the lists in parallel.

Has anyone heard of that before?

Ask HN: Is AI That Dangerous?
text:
Lots are saying we should be careful developing AI to avoid a Matrix/Terminator scenario. Keep it in the hands of the few with tight controls. Tethers, guardrails, etc.

Isn't it sufficient to simply pull the plug? I mean AI needs an computer and electricity to survive. Wheras we humans need oxygen and water. AI lives in the virtual world. We live in the physical world.

Can anyone convince me there is a real threat? Aside from "feep fakes" and "misinformation". Humans can do those very well already.

Ask HN: Online Writers Under 30?
text:
At first I was going to ask for “bloggers” under 30, because I’m really interested in seeing if there are any young people who have garnered a following through their own personal websites, but I suspect that to be kind of a rarity. I’ll settle also for anyone under 30 with a relatively popular Substack, or account on the Fediverse, or stuff like that.

Just please, no Twitter-ers.

But if you know anyone who satisfies my initial interest and doesn’t compose text content on Twitter, or is not a Vlogger, please share.

Popularity is not a necessity. I suspect that a lot of these writers may operate within certain niches. Niche followings are the among the best though. TIA.
